"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wux1665702922021.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wux1665702922021.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wux1665702922021.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wux1665702922021\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Performance Contention\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Concurrent processes might simultaneously allocate the same resources, such as certain parts of internal memory or specific rows of a table. Intensive use of the same resources by various processes cause contention and can decrease performance. In such situations, it is worthwhile to rearrange the application architecture so the required resources are allocated more selectively. An obvious way to do this is to reconsider the transaction definitions by minimizing the locking periods, the amount of locked data, or both.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wux1665702922021__p_d46409e1_d46410e1_d46411e1\">The following suggestions can also help reduce process contention:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wux1665702922021__li_d23120e1_d23121e1_d23122e1\">Attach components—use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/attach</span> switch when you create instances of Uniface forms, services, and reports. This ensures that all the attached child instances of the component are removed before the current instance exits, thereby freeing system resources.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wux1665702922021__li_d23123e1_d23124e1_d23125e1\">Avoid using the read/lock ProcScript instruction—the <code class=\"ph codeph\">read/lock</code> instruction results in paranoid locking. It is recommended that you avoid using this instruction for online transactions, because so many locks are required.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wux1665702922021__li_d23126e1_d23127e1_d23128e1\">Minimize the size of transactions.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533545\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533545\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Performance Contention Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Performance Contention Concurrent processes might simultaneously allocate the same resources, such as certain parts of internal memory or specific rows of a table. Intensive use of the same resources by various processes cause contention and can decrease performance. In such situations, it is worthwhile to rearrange the application architecture so the required resources are allocated more selectively. An obvious way to do this is to reconsider the transaction definitions by minimizing the locking periods, the amount of locked data, or both. The following suggestions can also help reduce process contention: Attach components—use the /attach switch when you create instances of Uniface forms, services, and reports. This ensures that all the attached child instances of the component are removed before the current instance exits, thereby freeing system resources. Avoid using the read/lock ProcScript instruction—the read/lock instruction results in paranoid locking. It is recommended that you avoid using this instruction for online transactions, because so many locks are required. Minimize the size of transactions. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}